data.meta_description: The Northern Michigan Wildcats men's ice hockey team is a National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) DivisionÂ I college ice hockey program that represents Northern Michigan University (NMU). The Wildcats are a member of the Central Collegiate Hockey Association (CCHA). NMU has won one national title and has made three Frozen Four appearances. They play at the Berry Events Center in Marquette, Michigan.
